<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-02-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="836" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d836">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216M/237.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-25"><hi rend="italic">February 25,
                                    1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Replying to Department’s telegram of the 22d instant Chargé Dearing
                            reports that the Mexican Government agrees to all the proposals
                            contained in that telegram.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>